[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring Scala 3 enums and Circe**\n\nI’m looking into whether Scala 3 enums are supported by the generic or semiauto features. It seems like testing an enum with cases could be useful. One thing I notice is that generic derivation for coproducts might treat case objects as strings. I wonder if deriving codecs for Scala 3 enums with parameterized cases could avoid duplicating sealed traits. It's intriguing that Circe's generics utilize Scala 3 Mirror, so it should be functional, but I’m also considering other features like custom field transforms and deriveKeyEncoder/Decoder.\n\n**Considering Scala 3 enums**\n\nI'm thinking there might be a potential issue with the Scala 3 enum, specifically with the singleton case `Complete`. I wonder if there are challenges related to encoding or decoding for this case. It seems like we can only work with parameterized cases right now, but shouldn't the feature of Scala 3 enums include singletons as well? Let's explore how this could be resolved or if it's just a quirk of the language.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0005a3089cc9fd8c016a28d6923548819691be8b3e9fc7fb46\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKNazf5R_4n8mp1PqGQmZTSykiakBz2LbP6YfbflSCpxmTNtpEofSTBTpe9Mjj2q22caTtRh031Una-yVHyyIxW94rotGD2Cfvq_YX2Wtc-d7VWF4nVWl1qbU3fPhjFBcdbWXqN1ddaeYjS4Kr-MSdrmcyrCNX_Jp7KY4cI-wqJmYVaoZdj0Ezx--XWsvhQUdSO6zgfKtX_WlLAPGa-eV75QGNRiVR2UZ_XFArMgjH-CQRUS7MnyR6t1ygElB3svdZxX-vkG1iAj0O7Yk_fe7MSeLHpOnXyoCEich3tRPh5dbf4l3wHK19CqY9xX2RRS4yjmZwGySEkfnPqC519xNQ5EW36AGQJ1c_3JXxGDpJvVY_hGHigzKsaHQBogsbDhVg64mqzdVIlVx-pJLcsDcfkiJT-NLFP4ZREgTjUDRtSOFvQSrV0oKF5dco6Gm05SYRtjFTZu6p5bKPcHKNl6uIIT6ntBVpCFSwagBffBH5kabRVFH8xU8KCMAx98t8efXki6s_CaUFvyKFFRvNP_asOsxRk9F6Bj74BCxQVIFwXBckBVauW_5TI_kyL7KR6t5Ef3Z-mygBKIjdAiDlUmbNr5D2mT_ESF_wDv-F0LU0HCZXXkcNxRfSQ2JUJ-iulQJN3-k_-Z5dOOjfCWjKolw2ByYYBvqheUKpElVBiYlg55-V-EGeN2QQ